body:
Some of the limits are easy to see, but I want to use Riemann integral to determine the value of the following limits. $\displaystyle\lim_{n\to\infty} \left(\frac{1}{n+1}+\frac{1}{n+2}+\cdots+\frac{1}{3n}\right)$ $\displaystyle\lim_{n\to\infty} \frac{1}{n} \sqrt[n]{(n+1)(n+2)\cdots(n+n)}$ $\displaystyle\lim_{n\to\infty} \left(\sin {\frac{n}{n^2+1^2}}+\sin {\frac{n}{n^2+2^2}}+\cdots+\sin {\frac{n}{n^2+n^2}}\right)$ For example in first, I suppose $\int_a^b f(x)dx$ is equal to the limit \begin{align}
\lim_{n\to\infty} \left(\frac{1}{n+1}+\frac{1}{n+2}+\cdots+\frac{1}{3n}\right) &= \lim_{n\to\infty} \sum_{i = 1}^{2n} \frac{1}{n+i} \\&= \lim_{n\to\infty}\sum_{i = 1}^{2n} f\left(a+\frac{(b-a)i}{2n}\right)\cdot\frac{(b-a)i}{n}
\end{align} But cannot find anything. Please don't tell me the method directly, I would appreciate it if you could give me some crucial hints for one\all of them. Thank you very much.
